<subSubSection pageId="181" pageNumber="182" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="181.[151,1437,1374,1725]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[272,516,1590,1617]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" pagination="165 - 197" refId="ref368231" refString="Rondani, C. (1850 c) Osservazioni sopra alquante specie di esapodi ditteri del Museo Torinese. Nuovi Annali delle Scienze Naturali e Rendiconto delle Sessioni della Societa Agraria e dell'Accademia delle Scienze dell'Istituto di Bologna, Series 3, 2, 165 - 197, 1 pl." type="journal article" year="1850">Rondani (1850c: 183)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1850" box="[636,904,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Rhagionidae" genus="Leptipalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis box="[636,904,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Leptipalpus brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from just the female sex, without specifying either the 
<taxonomicName box="[289,375,1627,1653]" family="Number" pageId="181" pageNumber="26" rank="family">number</taxonomicName>
or the length of the specimens, from material received from E. Truqui. 
<collectingRegion box="[1160,1239,1627,1653]" country="New Zealand" name="Nelson" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Nelson</collectingRegion>
Papavero labeled the single MRSN female as “ 
<typeStatus box="[524,627,1663,1689]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">holotype</typeStatus>
” but, as far as we know, he never indicated this specimen as 
<typeStatus box="[1309,1407,1663,1689]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">holotype</typeStatus>
in any of his publication. We consider it as a 
<typeStatus box="[674,761,1699,1725]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">syntype</typeStatus>
because Rondani did not specify he had a single specimen.
</paragraph>
